How do you pass markup or content from a parent to a child component using slots in LWC?
Companies that asked this: Salesforce, Microsoft, Google, Oracle, Adobe

Answer:
Slots are placeholders in child components that allow parents to pass markup content into specific areas.

Unnamed Slot:

<!-- Child Component -->
<template>
    <div class="card">
        <slot></slot> <!-- Content goes here -->
    </div>
</template>
<!-- Parent Component -->
<template>
    <c-card>
        <p>This content goes into the slot</p>
    </c-card>
</template>
Named Slots:

<!-- Child Component -->
<template>
    <header>
        <slot name="header">Default Header</slot>
    </header>
    <main>
        <slot>Default Content</slot>
    </main>
    <footer>
        <slot name="footer">Default Footer</slot>
    </footer>
</template>
<!-- Parent Component -->
<template>
    <c-layout>
        <h1 slot="header">Custom Header</h1>
        <p>Main content here</p>
        <div slot="footer">Footer content</div>
    </c-layout>
</template>


Key Points:

Unnamed slot: <slot></slot> - single content area

Named slots: <slot name="header"></slot> - multiple targeted areas

Default content: Child provides fallback if no content passed

Flexible composition: Parent controls what goes where



Interview Tips:

Explain slots are placeholders for parent-provided content

Show difference between named and unnamed slots

Mention default content capability

Emphasize flexible component composition benefits
